<item>
            <title>[SPR-2693] FreeMarkerConfigurer doesn&apos;t permit subclassing</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2693</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FreeMarkerConfigurer provides the following method:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	protected void postProcessTemplateLoaders(List templateLoaders) &lt;/p&gt;
{

		templateLoaders.add(new ClassTemplateLoader(getClass()));

		logger.info(&quot;ClassTemplateLoader for Spring macros added to FreeMarker configuration&quot;);

	}


&lt;p&gt;There are two issues here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. As the above method is not marked as &quot;final&quot;, it is reasonable to subclass. Subclassing does not work successfully due to the construction of ClassTemplateLoader. The getClass() method will return a class within the package of the subclass. If the package of the subclass differs from org.springframework.web.servlet.view.freemarker, the created ClassTemplateLoader will fail in finding spring.ftl.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. The ClassTemplateLoader(Class) constructor is deprecated (at least in FreeMarker 2.3.8).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To fix this issue (with FreeMarker 2.3.8) the revised method should be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	protected void postProcessTemplateLoaders(List templateLoaders) &lt;/p&gt;
{
		templateLoaders.add(new ClassTemplateLoader(FreeMarkerConfigurer.class, &quot;&quot;));
		logger.info(&quot;ClassTemplateLoader for Spring macros added to FreeMarker configuration&quot;);
	}

&lt;p&gt;The fix will thus always ensure the same package as where spring.ftl resides, and uses a new non-deprecated constructor.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
